cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for acquiring lexical semantic knowledge and disambiguation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses probabilistic models and the Minimum Description Length principle, which are common in machine learning and information theory, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with corpus data and word clustering, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CY).
